The paper deals with the complexity of the integer multiflow problem in planar graphs, which is a classic problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The problem involves routing demands between pairs of vertices in a graph subject to capacity constraints, and has applications in various areas of computer science and engineering. The paper specifically considers the case where there are only two demand edges on the infinite face of the routing graph, which is a natural and important special case. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), complexity theory (cs.NP), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and game theory (cs.GT).
